$1.5BEST.
IT Budget




Suncor Energy sells its products in the United States, Canada, and Europe. The company, formerly known as Suncor, Inc., was founded in 1953 and changed its name to Suncor Energy, Inc. With its subsidiaries, it operates as an integrated energy… MoreSuncor Energy sells its products in the United States, Canada, and Europe. The company, formerly known as Suncor, Inc., was founded in 1953 and changed its name to Suncor Energy, Inc. With its subsidiaries, it operates as an integrated energy company. It operates through four segments: Oil Sands, Natural Gas, Energy Marketing and Refining, and Refining and Marketing.

Suncor acquired Canadian Oil Sands in March, 2016. 
IT Structure:

• The IT department of Suncor is primarily centralized at the corporate headquarters in Calgary, Alberta. 
• Suncor's IT staff consists almost entirely of consultants contracted from IBM.
• Contract with EMC Documentum and IT vendor management. 
• The Information and Knowledge Management organization(IKM), though separate from… MoreIT Structure:

• The IT department of Suncor is primarily centralized at the corporate headquarters in Calgary, Alberta. 
• Suncor's IT staff consists almost entirely of consultants contracted from IBM.
• Contract with EMC Documentum and IT vendor management. 
• The Information and Knowledge Management organization(IKM), though separate from the internal IT, provides governance services, project delivery service and support, and change management.
• IKM recently partnered with Optimized Systems and Solutions, Inc. (OSys).

IT Intelligence:

2013:
• Implemented AVEVA NET to support and strengthen data security and analytics.





